         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>Reynolds points out that would be normal for a text cut within a metope to be self-contained; but 
               <ref target="https://igcyr.unibo.it/igcyr108500">IGCyr108500</ref> (not known to Reynolds at the time) provides a contrary example, and would support Oliverio's interpretation, and suggest a reference to a Flavian emperor.
               It seems just possible that we have here a female name Ματώι,
               and patronymic or husband's name in the genitive, Βεσπα; Ματω is attested in Asia Minor (so LGPN), but Βεσπας is not.</p><!-- check: ask cdl -->
         </div>
         
